{"questionId":"17844","questionHtml":"<p>Power <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is dissipated in a resistor of resistance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> when there is a direct current <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> in the resistor.</p>\n<p>What is the average power dissipation in a resistance&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;when the alternating root-mean-square (rms) current in the resistor is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>I</mi></math>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>P</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>P</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mi>P</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"17844","referenceCode":"20N.1.HL.TZ0.34","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Power P is dissipated in a resistor of resistance R when there is a direct current I in the resistor. What is the average power dissipation in a resistance R2 when the alternating ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"34","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.2 – Power generation and transmission","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}